title: About
text: I am a first generation college student, currently in my third-year as a statistics major at CSUMB. I am the captain of the men’s cross country and track and field teams, and enjoy enjoy exercise in the elements. For my campus day job, I am a tutor at the Cooperative Learning Center, providing illumination for STAT 250 students on the applications of statistics in science and technology. I am excited to start my first research experience with the NHGRI Great Scholar’s program over summer 2026, where I will be working at UCSC. In my free time, I enjoy going to the movies, hiking, traveling, and spending time with friends.
